President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring October 6, 2015, as German-American Day. The proclamation recognizes the contributions made by German Americans throughout history and highlights the strong partnership between the United States and Germany. It emphasizes the diverse talents and ideas brought by German Americans, who have played roles as architects, artists, inventors, engineers, and members of the Armed Forces. The proclamation also acknowledges the shared values and principles that bind the two nations together as allies, as they work together to address global challenges such as violent extremism, climate change, and gender equality. The proclamation encourages all Americans to learn more about the history and contributions of German Americans.